[2] USA (New Mexico)
Date: 25 Jul 2011
Source: News West 9 [edited]
http://www.newswest9.com/story/15144514/mckinley-county-man-dies-from-hantavirus


State health officials say a 23-year-old man from McKinley County has
died from hantavirus pulmonary syndrome.

The New Mexico Health Department said Monday [25 Jul 2011] that this
is the 4th hantavirus case reported in the state this year [2011].

Hantavirus is contracted by breathing particles of rodent droppings,
urine or saliva.

There's no specific treatment for hantavirus, but officials say the
chances for recovery are better with early medical attention.

The earlier cases this year [2011] consist of a 39-year-old McKinley
County man who recovered from the illness and a 51-year-old McKinley
County woman and a 35-year-old Torrance County man who both died from
hantavirus.

