[3] Chile (Aysen)
Date: Thu 28 Jul 2011
Source: El Diario de Aysen [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.diarioaysen.cl/noticias1.php?id=1463


According to Health SEREMI Claudio Vallejos, on Wednesday night [27
Jul 2011], a 71-year-old woman from the El Saldo area, between Aysen
and Chacabuco, died in the Coyhaique Regional Hospital after
presenting with a complex clinical picture for several days. The
examinations carried out on the patient in the hospital led to the
suspicion that she had a hantavirus infection.

In order to corroborate the preliminary diagnosis of a hantavirus
infection, health authorities sent medical samples to the Public
Health Institute in Santiago to carry out tests to confirm or discard
the [etiology of] the disease. Results will be ready this weekend
[30-31 Jul 2011].

The Health SEREMI indicated that a sanitary alert was activated 3
weeks ago in the Aysen region and Palena province due to the massive
presence of rodents. A confirmed hantavirus infection case was
released from hospital and is recuperating satisfactorily. Another
suspected case has been discarded.

It is worth remembering that preventive measures to deal with this
phenomenon are essential, such as good hygiene and keeping rodents
away. Maintain clean houses and patios, keep grass mown short, and
keep trash in hermetically sealed containers.

--
